Government of Maharashtra
Department of Medical Education and Pharmaceuticals,
Government Decision, No.: SHP-2025 / Q.No. 01 / Question-1,
Gokuldas Tejpal Hospital Complex, New G.T. Complex,
9th Floor, Mantralaya, Mumbai - 400 001.

Read: Letter No. of the Commissioner, Medical Education & AYUSH, State of Maharashtra, Mumbai: SAMVYASAVAS / BYJIPUNE / ETP STP 01811/13821 I-P / 24, dated 23.09.2024 Government Decision:

The construction budget for the installation of Effluent Treatment Plant (ETP) and Sewage Treatment Plant (STP) in the premises of B. G. Government Medical College and Sassoon General Hospital, Pune under the Department is being accorded administrative sanction for an amount of Rs. 12,97,95, 230 / - (Rupees Twelve Crores, Ninety Five Thousand, Two Hundred and Thirty Only) (inclusive of all taxes) subject to the following conditions.
1) The ownership of the land should be settled before the work is done.
2) If the work is under the jurisdiction of the Archaeological Department, prior permission of the concerned department as well as the Municipal Corporation and similar authorities should be taken.
3) In granting technical approval, action should be taken in accordance with Government Circular No. 2017 / Q. 11 / Planning-3, dated 11.04.2017 for processing of matters outside the State Rates.

4) Suggestions issued under the Government Decision dated 24.08.2017 from the Department of Industry, Power and Labour should be considered by adopting the e-tendering system for procurement related matters in the proposal.
5) Department of Environment, Government Decisions, ENV-2013 / P.S. No. 177 / Hr. Action should be taken as per the guidelines mentioned in No. 1, dated 10th January, 2014.
6) These works should be completed during the construction period itself by proper planning of electrification as well as other ancillary works.
